on JDK 25. It’s important to be cautious since meaningful coverage requires the right setup. The failure may come from multipart issues or denied access, so I should check the exception logs for further insights.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring configurations**\\n\\nI’m considering whether there's a need for a Docker image here. The WebClient can connect to the in-process Vert.x HttpServer, and while documentation mentions it’s for external services, it can still work for testing the local server. I should remember not to restate deterministic entries as guidance. As for dependencies, the optional vertx-auth-oauth2 is only necessary for OAuth2 authentication methods. However, meaningful coverage of the core functionality doesn’t require it, so I can proceed without it.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"io.vertx:vertx-web-client:5.0.1 depends on Vert.x 5.0.1, which manages Netty 4.2.2.Final. Existing 5.0.0 tests already document that Netty 4.2.x needs explicit unsafe/reflection access for Java 25 native runs; 5.0.1 remains in that Netty line, so generated tests should preserve that runtime setup.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"For native-image test execution on JDK 25, configure native test runtime system properties equivalent to: -Dsun.misc.unsafe.memory.access=allow and -Dio.netty.tryReflectionSetAccessible=true. WebClient coverage can use an in-process Vert.x HttpServer on localhost; no external service or Docker image is required.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The existing 5.0.0 Gradle setup applies these native runtime args only when libraryVersion == '5.0.0'; a generated 5.0.1 test that inherits that condition may reproduce the native-image run failure.\",\n    \"Optional Vert.x modules such as vertx-auth-oauth2 are declared optional and are only needed for OAuth-specific scenarios, not for meaningful core WebClient coverage.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "